</ul>

<h4><a name="_Ref10356744">Logging on to Sierra Online</a></h4>

<p>The Login panel (located in the upper left) allows you to log on to Sierra Online.  You must
specify your user name and password before clicking the <i>Login</i> button.  If you do not have a
Sierra Online user name, click the <a href=#_Ref10356796><i>Create New User</i></a> button to create one.
If this is your first login on this computer for this user name, the
<a href=#_Ref10356800>Terms of Use</a> dialog will appear; you must agree to the Terms of Use
before you can continue.</p>

<p>Note that the <i>Username</i> edit box
remembers previous user names.  You can use the drop down arrow to select one.  You may also click
the <i>Remember Password</i> check box to save your password for future logins.</p>

<p>The <i>Login</i> button will be unavailable if you do not have an active Internet connection or
if you are unable to contact the Sierra Online servers.

<p>Logging in will take you to the lobby server and room you were last in, if possible, or to an
appropriate default lobby server/room if not.  If you hold down the <i>control</i> key when you click
the <i>Login</i> button, you will be able to select a room rather than automatically joining.</p>

<p><a href=#_RefTop>Return to top</a></p>

<h4><a name="_Ref10356796">Creating Sierra Online Accounts</a></h4>

<p>To create a Sierra Online Account, click the <i>Create New
User</i> button in the Login panel (located in the upper left). The Create Account panel will
display on the right side of the screen.  The following fields will need to be entered:</p>

<ul type=circle>
<li><p><i>User Name</i>.  Enter your desired user name.  
User names must be at least two characters long and may not contain leading or
trailing spaces, multiple embedded spaces, non-printable characters,
or any of the following characters: ‘ “ `@ / \ | ? % .  <b><i>It is highly recommended that you
do not use your real name when selecting your user name.</i></b></p></li>

<li><p><i>Password</i>.  Enter your desired password.  Passwords must
be at least 4 characters long.  They may
contain any character.  A combination of
alphabetic, numeric, and punctuation is recommended for good security.</p></li>

<li><p><i>Re-enter Password.</i>  Confirm your password.  This must
match what you entered in <i>Password</i> exactly.</p></li>

<li><p><i>E-mail Account.</i>  Enter your e-mail address.  It
must be of the form <i>a@b.c</i>  (where <i>a</i>, <i>b</i>, and <i> c</i> are any
  text).  Your e-mail address is used to
send you any forgotten passwords or accounts.</p></li>

<li><p><i>Birthdate. </i>Enter your date of birth.  You must be 13 years of age or older to play
on Sierra Online.</p></li>

<li><p><i>Sierra Offers and Information.</i>  Check this box if you wish to receive
information and special offers from Sierra via e-mail.  Note that the default is unchecked.</p></li>
</ul>

<p>Once all fields have been filled in
with a valid value, the <i>Create</i> button will enable.  Click on <i>Create </i>to have the account
created for use.  The <a href=#_Ref10356800>Terms of Use</a> dialog will
now appear; you must agree to the Terms of Use before you can create an account.</p>

<p><a href=#_RefTop>Return to top</a></p>

<h4><a name="_Ref10356800">Terms of Use Dialog</a></h4>

<p>The Terms of Use dialog is displayed whenever a new account is created or the first time
an existing is account is used to log on to Sierra Online on your computer.  You must accept
the terms of use before you may log on or create accounts.  Click the
<i>I agree to the terms of use</i> check box to signify your agreement.  Once checked,
you may click the <i>Accept</i> button to continue.  If you do not agree to the terms of use, you may
click the <i>Reject</i> button to return to the login screen.</p>

<p><a href=#_RefTop>Return to top</a></p>

<h4><a name="_Ref10356806">LAN and Direct Connection Play</a></h4>

<p>For LAN and/or Direct Connection play, select the <i>Other
Multiplayer</i> button in the Status panel (located in the lower right).  This will take you
to the screens for other types of multiplayer.  You may select the <i>Help</i> tab on these screens
for additional information.</p>

<p><a href=#_RefTop>Return to top</a></p>

<h4><a name="_Ref10356824">Retrieving Lost Passwords</a></h4>

<p>To retrieve a lost password for a Sierra Online account,
click the <i>Lost Password</i> button in the Options panel (located in the
lower left).  The Lost Password panel will display on the right side of the screen.  You must
enter a user name to retrieve a password for before the <i>Retrieve
Password</i> button will enable.  (Or
you can select a user name using the drop down list.)  Once a user name has been entered,
click <i>Retrieve Password</i>.</p>

<p>Passwords are e-mailed to the e-mail account registered with the Sierra Online
account.  Passwords can only be requested once per 24 hours per account.</p>

<p><a href=#_RefTop>Return to top</a></p>

<h4><a name="_Ref10356831">Retrieving Lost Usernames</a></h4>

<p>To retrieve a lost username(s) for a Sierra Online
account(s), click the <i>Lost Username</i> button in the Options panel (located
in the lower left).  The Lost Username
panel will display on the right side of the screen.  You must enter an e-mail address
of the form <i>a@b.c</i> 
(where <i>a</i>, <i>b</i>, and <i> c</i> are any text) before the <i>Retrieve Username(s)</i> button
will enable.  Once an e-mail address has
been entered, click <i>Retrieve Username(s)</i>.</p>

<p>All usernames for the specified
e-mail address will be e-mailed to that address.  Usernames can only be requested
once per 24 hours per account.</p>

<p><a href=#_RefTop>Return to top</a></p>

<h4><a name="_Ref10356837">Other Options</a></h4>

<p>The Login Screen supplies the following additional options:</p>

<ul type=circle>
<li><p><i>Announcements Button</i>.  Located in the Options panel, the <i>Announcements</i> button
displays the Announcements panel on the right side of the screen.  This panel contains
any important information regarding online play.</p></li>

<li><p><i>Help Button</i>.  Located in the Options panel in the lower left, the <i>Help</i> button
displays the Help panel on the right side of the screen.</p></li>

<li><p><i>Back Button</i>.  Located at the bottom right, the <i>Back</i> button exits multiplayer and
returns you to the main menu.</p></li>

<li><p><i>Status Panel</i>.  Located at the bottom, the Status panel displays any status and progress
messages.</p></li>
</ul>

<p><a href=#_RefTop>Return to top</a></p>

<h4><a name="_RefInitFail">Initialization Failure</a></h4>

<p>If there are problems validating your Internet connection or initializing for online play, the
<i>Initialization Failure Panel</i> displays in place of the <a href=#_Ref10356744>Login Panel</a>,
and the <a href=#_Ref10356837>Status Panel</a> will display "<i>Failed to initialize online system.</i>&quot;&nbsp;
The <i>Initialization Failure Panel</i> displays a summary of the problem, a <i>Retry</i> button, and
possibly an <i>Ignore</i> button (depending on the type of error).  Pressing Retry will attempt
initialization again.  Pressing Ignore will continue on as if the error did not occur (your
mileage may vary).</p>

<p>Possible conditions that may cause initialization failure:</p>

<ul type=circle>
<li><p><b>You do not appear to be connected to the Internet</b>.  No active Internet connection could
be detected for your computer.  Please make sure you are connected to the Internet before attempting to
play online.  Note that you can <i>ignore</i> this error and attempt to play online anyway.</p></li>

<li><p><b>Unable to locate master servers...</b>.  No servers for Sierra Online could be found.
You should verify your Internet connection is available.  Also check the <i>Announcements</i> to see
if any maintenance is scheduled.  Check with your ISP to see if they are experiencing any issues.  If
all else fails, contact technical support.</p></li>

<li><p><b>Communication failure with master servers...</b>.  An error has occurred
  while communicating
with the servers for Sierra Online.  Check the <i>Announcements</i> to see if any maintenance is
scheduled.  If all else fails, contact technical support.</p></li>

<li><p><b>Unable to locate: ...</b>.  Certain types of servers for playing via Sierra Online could not
be found.  You may or may not be able to <i>ignore</i> this problem depending on the types of servers.
Check the <i>Announcements</i> to see if any maintenance if scheduled. If all else fails, contact
technical support.</p></li>

<li><p><b>Communication failure with version servers: ...</b>.  An error has occurred
  while communicating
with the version checking servers for Sierra Online.  Check the <i>Announcements</i> to see if any
maintenance is scheduled.  If all else fails, contact technical support.</p></li>
</ul>


